* Miriam Cabeza as Edurne
* Santi Ugalde as Kepa
* [[Los del Río]] as themselves

==Box office==
The weekend of its premiere, the film gathered an audience of 404,020 which resulted in box office grossing of 2.72 million euros.<ref>{{cite web|author=por José A. Romero |url=http://www.elcorso.es/ocho-apellidos-vascos-coge-la-ola-de-lo-posible/ |title=‘Ocho apellidos vascos’ coge la ola de ‘lo posible’ - El Corso |publisher=Elcorso.es |date= |accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref> On its second weekend its grossing increased by 56%, third best behind ''[[The Impossible (2012 film)|The Impossible]]'' and ''[[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]]'' in its first ten days with a total 4.4 million euros.<ref>{{cite web|author=elcorreo.com |url=http://www.elcorreo.com/vizcaya/20140317/mas-actualidad/cultura/ocho-apellidos-vascos-recaudado-201403170943.html |title='Ocho apellidos vascos' revienta la taquilla. El Correo |work=Elcorreo.com |date= |accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref> By April it became the most watched Spanish film in Spain with more than 6.5 million viewers and the second film with the greatest box office grossing in Spain, only behind ''[[Avatar (2009 film)|Avatar]]'', with a box-office of more than 45 million euros (more than 62 million dollars).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://cultura.elpais.com/cultura/2014/03/24/actualidad/1395663646_520785.html |title=‘Ocho apellidos vascos’ duplica su taquilla en su segundo fin de semana &#124; Cultura &#124; EL PAÍS |work=Cultura.elpais.com |date=2014-03-24 |accessdate=2014-04-27}}</ref> It has grossed {{USD|77 million}} in Spain<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/box-office-8-international-hits-759118|title= Box Office: 8 International Hits That Challenged the Studio Tentpoles |author= Scott Roxborough|date=2014-12-22|accessdate= 2014-12-22|work= [[The Hollywood Reporter]]}}</ref> and a total of {{USD|78.7 million}} internationally.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://deadline.com/2015/01/top-100-films-international-box-office-2014-transformers-1201343914/|title= ‘Transformers 4′ Tops 2014’s 100 Highest-Grossing International Films – Chart|author= Nancy Tartaglione and David Bloom|date= January 10, 2015|accessdate= January 10, 2015|work= [[Deadline Hollywood]]}}</ref>

== Critical reception ==
The critics were divided about the film, but were mostly positive. For magazine ''[[Cinemanía]]'', Carlos Marañón stressed that the movie was "extremely funny".<ref>{{cite web|author=Cinemanía|author-link=Cinemanía|title=Ocho apellidos vascos|url=http://cinemania.es/criticas-de-cine/ocho-apellidos-vascos|accessdate=12 May 2014}}</ref> This comment was repeated in many reviews that highlighted the film is "funny",<ref name="ABC">{{cite web|author=Diario ABC|title=Crítica de "Ocho apellidos vascos" (***): Euskadi tiene un sabor especial|url=http://hoycinema.abc.es/critica/20140314/abci-ocho-apellidos-vascos-opiniones-201403131323.html|accessdate=12 May 2014}}</ref> and for some, "inspired and bright".<ref name=Vanguardia>{{cite web|author=La Vanguardia|title="8 apellidos vascos": Bienvenidos al norte|url=http://www.lavanguardia.com/cine/20140314/54403629811/8-apellidos-vascos-critica-de-cine.html|accessdate=12 May 2014}}</ref> Federico Marin Bellon journalist of  ''[[ABC (newspaper)|ABC]]'', spoke of a "brave and timely movie",<ref name="ABC" /> highlighting another aspect, the opportunity of its theme, which has also been emphasized by most critics who often compared it to the French film ''[[Bienvenue chez les Ch'tis|Welcome to the Sticks]]''. For ''[[El País]]'', Borja Valero even predicted it could be the movie of the year.<ref>{{cite web|author=El País|title=España/Euskadi: la película|url=http://cultura.elpais.com/cultura/2014/03/24/actualidad/1395667742_278430.html|accessdate=12 May 2014}}</ref>

Regarding the actors, in general, the work of the cast has been well received by critics .

On the negative side, Luis Martínez from ''[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]'', said that the film is "a bad comedy"<ref>{{cite web|author=El Mundo|title=Por fin unas risas con el País Vasco|url=http://www.elmundo.es/cronica/2014/03/23/532d537722601d57208b4570.html}}</ref> while Jordi Costa, from daily newspaper ''El País'', said the development was irregular and ended catastrophically. Fausto Fernandez, in the magazine ''Fotogramas'', labelled it as impersonal and described its development as flat.<ref>{{cite web|author=Fotogramas|author-link=Fotogramas|title=Ocho apellidos vascos|url=http://www.fotogramas.es/Peliculas/Ocho-apellidos-vascos/Critica|accessdate=6 June 2014}}</ref>

The film has a 6.2 average in FilmAffinity and 6.9 on IMDb.

